<blockquote>When you buy or sell an option, there is almost always a dealer on the other side of the trade, and that dealer is implicitly taking the inverse of your position. Because the dealer doesn't want the directional risk associated with that position, he hedges by taking a dynamic position in the underlying. The goal of that position is to replicate, as nearly as possible, the exact payoff of the option. So, for example, if you buy an at-the-money (ATM) put from a dealer, that dealer will start by short- selling about 50% of the notional value of the position (this is a 50-delta put). Then, if the underlying goes down, he will short-sell more; and if it goes up, he will cover (buy back) some of the short. </blockquote>"},{"pid":"a4c8f56187e61097acd4ecc5b2c04233fbea17ff","tid":2416550,"uid":198089,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2021-02-21T11:51:16.000Z","msg":"鹽巴 <br />\n我睇書又玩paper trade <img src=\"/assets/faces/cat/bye.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/cat/bye.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/cat/bye.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"a2c00a2fcb529fa75ccb71fd01ae508418aa1222","tid":2416550,"uid":326779,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"ffec7df291267d2d0c7dbcb9cdda6e8ce54a60b3","tid":2416550,"uid":214177,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2021-02-21T10:08:54.000Z","msg":"多謝賜教 <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/hoho.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><br />\n玩咗幾年美股 係呢一年先玩多咗期權<br />\n發覺難玩好多<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> 所以都係對沖為主<br />\n呢排波動大 我用咗大概一半股數sc價外對沖<br />\n我嘅諗法係萬一升到價內行權就當自己賣早咗<br />\n萬一跌就當執期權金<br />\n好想知道我有冇隱藏風險忽視咗<br />\n可唔可以俾d意見 <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},"citedBy":2,"replyTime":"2021-02-21T13:37:23.000Z","msg":"你個風險就係你隻野升到飛天你無份食或者係急跌你平唔平sc cut loss. 如果做covered call 好似無敵， 但其實你個資產下跌係血淋淋既損失。"},{"pid":"384d5123ec802eced1bbc08a9f9b6883bdaa28d8","tid":2416550,"uid":326779,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0